    "MissionGiver": "Hockrow Agency",
    "Title": "Jorrit Dossier: Project Hyperion",
    "Description": "Hockrow Agency \nCase File #JD10285\nLead Investigator: Arken Mallor\n\nCase Update: \nAll your digging around Onyx has paid off. I\u2019ve been able to confirm that Jorrit has been operating an off-the-record lab in the facility\u2019s Site-B in order to conduct an experiment he calls \u201cProject Hyperion.\u201d I\u2019ll send his <EM4>lab notes to your mobiGlas journal</EM4> once you\u2019re underway, but the long and short of it is the bastard is trying to make Humans evolve or some nonsense like that.\n\nThe client wants the experimental data, so you\u2019re going back to Onyx and do everything needed to get Project Hyperion up and running. \n\nContract Investigator Actions:\nPrep the experiment by collecting a <EM4>Reagent code from the Engineering wing</EM4> and a <EM4>Catalyst code from the Research wing</EM4>.\n\nOnce you have those, head down to the <EM4>Lab in Site-B</EM4> and <EM4>run the experiment</EM4> so you can <EM4>upload the results</EM4>.\n\nAdditional Notes:\nSince this is an active lab, there might be ASD security on-site.\n \nTravel to Onyx in a vehicle that can be stored in a large hangar.",
